com.versant.var
Class VARTxData

java.lang.Object
  com.versant.var.VARTxData

public class VARTxData
extends java.lang.Object

Interface for API based replication VARTxData creates a replication request and adds the request to the persistent request queue (The persistent request queue is processed by the replication server). A request contains loids of the objects to be replicated. Objects belonging to more than one channel can be replicated in one transaction. Name of the channel for a group of objects is specified by the user. There should be only one VARTxData object per session. Method "prepareToEndTransaction" should be called before ending the transaction, i.e. irrsepective of whether a transaction is committed or rolled back. For TransSession and ODMG session, only plain commit can be used. For FundSession, it is recommended that you use plain commit but if any other flavour of commit, for e.g. xactwithvstr, checkpoint commit is used then the objects added in the "commitObjects" HandleVector should be committed withthe commit, locks should be released and the objects should be released from the cache. Static methods Initialize Cleanup getCurrent should be used only in multi threaded - multi session environment. If these methods are used then don't use any constructor to create VARTxData object.

prepareToEndTransaction

public void prepareToEndTransaction(java.lang.String db,
                                    com.versant.fund.HandleVector commitObjects)
Description copied from class: VARTxData
prepareToEndTransaction Creates persistent request object which is used by the replication server to replicate the objects. call this method before commit. For TransSession and ODMG session, only plain commit can be used. For FundSession, it is recommended that you use plain commit. But if any other form ofcommit is used(such as checkpoint commit) then ensure that objects added in the commitObjects should be committed, locks should be released after the commit and objects are released from the cache.

Parameters:
db - Name of the database in which replication request is created.
commitObjects - objects created/updated by this method
